{
  "text": "Generally, polymer and liposome based gene tranfection can only achieve a transient gene and protein expressions around 14 days in vitro [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This time window is sufficient and safe for therapeutic angiogenesis for treatment of ischemic heart disease or ischemic limb disease [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , as localized and prolonged over-expression of angiogenic factor has been shown to cause angioma [CITATION_5] . In addition to polymer or liposome, PEGylated liposomal nanoparticles which have been shown to have high gene transfection with HEK293 in vitro [CITATION_6] , may have the potent to transfect hiPSC-CMs efficiently.",
  "correct_citation": {
